text.tspan: In the wireframes and user flow, it was
imperative to stay true to the iconic UI
elements of Tinder and the mechanics of
the swipe features.
In this user flow, the user is frustrated
with their matches and has an existing
Tinder account. The user sends a link to
their friend to help in the matchmaking
process. The onboarding process for
matchmakers is illustrated on the right.
Once the matchmakers have onboarded,
they can start swiping, as per normally
done on Tinder. The matchmaker can go
to their messages to chat with candidates
to set up dates, or unmatch them.
Regarding the matchmakers, creating the
wireframes and mapping the user flow
helped identify potential issues on where
this feature will physically be within the
app, as well as how matchmakers (who
potentially have Tinder accounts) can
switch between their own personal
account, and the matchmaker one.

text.tspan: A new feature where users could
opt to verify their accounts was
added.
This feature is added in at the
log-in stage where the user goes
through a mini-onboarding and
has the choice to take a photo/
upload their ID.
Once the users ID is verified, a
blue tick will appear next to
their name, indicating that their
profile has been verified.
Users will be prompted after this
stage to go to the swiping page.
